Date: 4 Oct 2017
Source: OIE [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?reportid=24940


Anthrax - Tanzania
---------------------
Information received on 4 Oct 2017 from Dr Abdu A. Hayghaimo, Director, Veterinary Services, Ministry of Livestock and Fisheries Development, Dar Es Salaam, Tanzania

Summary
Report type: Follow-up report No. 1
Date of start of the event: 8 Sep 2017
Date of confirmation of the event: 13 Sep 2017
Report date: 4 Oct 2017
Date submitted to OIE: 4 Oct 2017
Reason for notification: Recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 7 Feb 2017
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to: a defined zone within the country.

Related reports: Immediate notification (22 Sep 2017)
Follow-up report No. 1 (4 Oct 2017)

Outbreaks: There are no new outbreaks in this report.

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive; Contact with infected animal(s) at grazing/watering

Epidemiological comments: The occurrence of the disease was limited to one camp, and the situation appears to be sufficiently stable. No new cases in either hippopotamus or other wild ruminants have been recorded ever since.

Control measures
Measures applied: Official disposal of carcasses, by-products and waste; Zoning; Disinfection; Vaccination prohibited; No treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: Surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone; Surveillance within containment and/or protection zone

Future Reporting: The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

--
